      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " عَلِيّاً ( صلوات الله عليه ) أُتِيَ بِالْكُوفَةِ بِرَجُلٍ سَرَقَ حَمَاماً فَلَمْ يَقْطَعْهُ وَ قَالَ لَا قَطْعَ فِي الطَّيْرِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Muhammad Bin Yahya Al Khazzaz, from Gayas Bin Ibrahim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> that Ali<sup>asws</sup>, they came to him<sup>asws</sup> with a man at Al-Kufa who had stolen a dove. So he<sup>asws</sup> did not cut him, and said: ‘There is no cutting (of the hand) regarding the bird’."
        ]
      }
